<subSubSection id="F0DE654CFFB1671E00A426C3FF50FA49" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B87B36C7FFB1671E00A426C3FD3EFA1F" blockId="5.[151,1436,1016,2014]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FFB1671E00A426C3FD9EFBA3" bold="true" box="[151,563,1016,1042]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Generic diagnosis. Adult female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="20FF2A42FFB1671E027626C2FD20FBA2" box="[581,653,1017,1043]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,256,1842,1866]" captionTargetBox="[261,1329,361,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-148@6.[249,1337,346,1818]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Acanthococcus aceris Signoret. Adult female, where A = marginal spinose seta; B = dorsal microtubular duct; C = dorsal spinose seta; D = dorsal macrotubular duct; K = ventral loculate pore; L = cruciform pore; M = frontal lobe; N = claw of metathoracic leg; R = larger ventral macrotubular duct; S = intermediate-sized macrotubular duct, T = small macrotubular duct; V = ventral seta (modified after Williams, 1985)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5313328" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5313328/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). 
<materialsCitation id="08AC3C9AFFB1671E029B26C2FD22FA1F" collectionCode="VII, VIII" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
Surface covered in waxy ovisac. 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FFB1671E040F26C2FB31FBA3" box="[1084,1180,1017,1042]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Dorsum</emphasis>
. Derm membranous. Setae often enlarged and spinose but highly variable among species. Enlarged tubular ducts absent. Macrotubular ducts present throughout. Microtubular ducts present, of varied structure. Loculate pores rarely present. Cruciform pores absent. Anal lobes well developed and often sclerotised; frequently with teeth-like projections on inner margins. Median plate present. Anal ring well developed with pores and setae. 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FFB1671E050E21B4FA31FB19" box="[1341,1436,1167,1192]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Margin.</emphasis>
Often clearly demarcated by a line of enlarged spinose setae. 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FFB1671E03B9218FFC7BFB7C" box="[906,982,1204,1229]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Venter</emphasis>
. Setae often spinose near margin but hairlike elsewhere. Macrotubular ducts present, frequently of more than 
<specimenCount id="AEC2FD4EFFB1671E043221E2FBFDFB42" box="[1025,1104,1241,1267]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="generic" typeStatus="type">1 type</specimenCount>
. Microducts, when present, usually restricted to near margins; similar to those on dorsum in structure. Loculate pores present, usually with 5 loculi. Cruciform pores usually present. Frontal lobes present; antennal tubercles absent. Antennae usually 6 or 7 segmented. Labium 3 segmented, basal segment with 2 pairs of setae. Legs well developed; claw and tarsal digitules with apical knobs; claw with denticle; hind legs usually with translucent pores. Vulva present between abdominal segments 
<collectionCode id="DED5AE02FFB1671E01C420AFFDB2FA1F" box="[503,543,1428,1454]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">VII</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode id="DED5AE02FFB1671E026A20AFFD22FA1F" box="[601,655,1428,1454]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">VIII</collectionCode>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B87B36C7FFB1671E00F52082FF50FA49" blockId="5.[151,1436,1016,2014]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">The species from the Neotropics currently included in this genus are found on a wide range of plant families.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F0DE654CFFB1671C00F52338FB63FCB6" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B87B36C7FFB1671D00F52338FE69FE93" blockId="5.[151,1436,1016,2014]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1436,152,290]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FFB1671E00F52338FEE4F9AC" bold="true" box="[198,329,1539,1565]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Comment.</emphasis>
Currently 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FFB1671E01E6233FFD2BF9AC" box="[469,646,1540,1565]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Cystocloniaceae" genus="Acanthococcus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gigartinales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FFB1671E01E6233FFD2BF9AC" box="[469,646,1540,1565]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Acanthococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a world-wide distribution, but the identity and number of species that are closely related to the 
<typeStatus id="677F8865FFB1671E02792312FDD1F9F2" box="[586,636,1577,1603]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FFB1671E02D32312FCEAF9F3" box="[736,839,1577,1602]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Cystocloniaceae" genus="Acanthococcus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gigartinales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="species" species="aceris">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FFB1671E02D32312FCEAF9F3" box="[736,839,1577,1602]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">A. aceris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will not be known until more detailed analyses are undertaken. Following the work of 
<bibRefCitation id="DC554B36FFB1671E027F2375FCCBF9D9" author="Cook, L. G. &amp; Gullan, P. J." box="[588,870,1614,1640]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="441 - 452" refId="ref48753" refString="Cook, L. G. &amp; Gullan, P. J. (2004) The gall-inducing habit has evolved multiple times among the eriococcid scale insects (Sternorrhyncha: Coccoidea: Eriococcidae). Biological Journal of the Linnean Society, 83, 441 - 452." type="journal article" year="2004">Cook &amp; Gullan (2004)</bibRefCitation>
, it is here considered that all species from the Neotropics currently placed in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FFB1671E02B8234FFCBFF93C" authorityName="Targioni Tozzetti" authorityYear="1868" box="[651,786,1652,1677]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FFB1671E02B8234FFCBFF93C" box="[651,786,1652,1677]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Eriococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are more appropriately placed in 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FFB1671E049E234FFACFF93C" box="[1197,1378,1652,1677]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Cystocloniaceae" genus="Acanthococcus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gigartinales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FFB1671E049E234FFACFF93C" box="[1197,1378,1652,1677]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Acanthococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see Appendix 1) excluding those recently placed in 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FFB1671E02EF23A2FC16F903" box="[732,955,1689,1714]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriobalachowskya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FFB1671E02EF23A2FC16F903" box="[732,955,1689,1714]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Eriobalachowskya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FFB1671E03C423A2FED5F969" authority="(Kozar &amp; Konczne Benedicty, 2008)" baseAuthorityName="Kozar &amp; Konczne Benedicty" baseAuthorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Hempelicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FFB1671E03C423A2FB00F903" box="[1015,1197,1689,1714]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Hempelicoccus</emphasis>
(Kozár &amp; Konczné Benedicty, 2008)
</taxonomicName>
. However, because most South American species in 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FFB1671E040E2384FB62F969" authorityName="Targioni Tozzetti" authorityYear="1868" box="[1085,1231,1727,1752]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FFB1671E040E2384FB62F969" box="[1085,1231,1727,1752]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Eriococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were placed in 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FFB1671E00A423DFFEE7F94C" box="[151,330,1764,1789]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Cystocloniaceae" genus="Acanthococcus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gigartinales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FFB1671E00A423DFFEE7F94C" box="[151,330,1764,1789]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Acanthococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="DC554B36FFB1671E014B23DFFD00F94F" author="Miller, D. R. &amp; Gimpel, M. E." box="[376,685,1764,1790]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refId="ref51225" refString="Miller, D. R. &amp; Gimpel, M. E. (2000) A Systematic Catalogue of the Eriococcidae (Felt Scales) (Hemiptera: Coccoidea) of the World. Intercept, Andover, UK, 589 pp." type="book" year="2000">Miller and Gimpel (2000)</bibRefCitation>
or Kozár &amp; Konczné Benedicty (2008), new combinations are required only for 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FFB1671E01402232FDD9F892" authority="Gonzalez" authorityName="Gonzalez" box="[371,628,1801,1827]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Cystocloniaceae" genus="Acanthococcus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gigartinales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="species" species="clapsae">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FFB1671E01402232FE59F893" box="[371,500,1801,1826]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">E. clapsae</emphasis>
González
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FFB1671E02B12232FC02F892" authority="Gonzalez" authorityName="Gonzalez" box="[642,943,1801,1827]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Cystocloniaceae" genus="Acanthococcus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gigartinales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="species" species="cuneifoliae">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FFB1671E02B12232FC82F893" box="[642,815,1801,1826]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">E. cuneifoliae</emphasis>
González
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FFB1671E038E2232FB46F892" authority="Gonzalez" authorityName="Gonzalez" box="[957,1259,1801,1827]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="divericatae">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FFB1671E038E2232FBC6F893" box="[957,1131,1801,1826]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">E. divericatae</emphasis>
González
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FFB1671E04CA2232FEA4F8F9" authority="Gonzalez" authorityName="Gonzalez" class="Florideophyceae" family="Cystocloniaceae" genus="Acanthococcus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gigartinales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="species" species="pituilensis">
